The paper discusses a method for optimizing machine learning pipelines using genetic programming, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on introducing imputation methods as part of the optimization process, which involves dealing with missing data, a problem that falls under the category of data management (cs.DM). The proposed approach also involves enforcing constraints in the generation of the GP trees, which is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
